The Feedback=E2=80=A6

My interview last Monday with new Paramount owner David Ellison sparked a f=
lurry of messages. Some highlights=E2=80=A6

=E2=80=9CThanks for a great interview with David Ellison. Much of what he s=
poke about in terms of goals was refreshing. However, as a woman at this co=
mpany, I have concerns that two members of his leadership, John Lasseter an=
d Jeff Shell, have been removed from past positions due to sexual harassmen=
t allegations. This feels like an irresponsible and distressing move by a y=
oung leader.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A Paramount employee

=E2=80=9CI think your =E2=80=98Peak Nepo Baby=E2=80=99 comment would have r=
ubbed me entirely the wrong way if I were Ellison, and for good reason. Yes=
, the deal may have been overvalued (on current paper), and yes, you went o=
n to say a couple of nice things. But rather than (or in addition to)
writing theories on the investment financials and motives, it would have be=
en only fair to point out Ellison=E2=80=99s achievements in this business (=
other than waiting around for a deal like this).=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94An actor

=E2=80=9CDuring negotiations on a pitch, =E2=80=A6 David called me (from hi=
s plane) to talk through a story point. For half an hour. Name another stud=
io owner who would do that.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A writer

=E2=80=9C=EF=BB=BFSome obvious moves for Ellison and Skydance to make in th=
e near future:

* Sell off BET and Showtime if Shari & Co. don=E2=80=99t get to it first
* Make the NFL the centerpiece of CBS and use the entire company=E2=80=99s =
product suite and distribution network to extract more value out of the cos=
tly media rights
* Reorient D2C around Kids, Sports, and News, which would actually make it =
a
differentiated service rather than Netflix=E2=80=99s downtrodden kid brothe=
r
* Scripted content partnerships (likely overseas) with Netflix, Peacock, or=
 Apple TV+.
* Reinvest in Nickelodeon, which remains an undervalued programming asset.
* Hammer the P.R. angle that Ellison is =E2=80=98saving=E2=80=99 a legacy s=
tudio (and, by extension, investing in creative talent) to generate as much=
 goodwill as possible to offset any negative feedback to a necessary aggres=
sive embrace of cost-cutting A.I.
* Position Pluto TV as a minor replacement for R.S.N.s. FAST can=E2=80=99t =
replicate the economics of R.S.N.s, of course, but at least these services =
already have a foothold and focus on local/regional programming versus the =
national/global-minded major SVODs.
* Try to steal a few name brand boutique production outfits =C3=A0 la Blumh=
ouse, Monkeypaw, Village Roadshow, etc., away from rivals via first-look/ov=
erall deals to prioritize quality, cost-effective theatrical bets.=E2=80=9D
=E2=80=94An analyst

