         <tr class=3D"replica" name=3D"s9">
          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">While Netflix and E=
delman maintain final cut of the film, the Netflix deal with the estate cal=
ls for a <i>six-hour </i>series, and Edelman delivered <i>nine hours</i>. T=
he estate has been using that violation of the agreement to essentially hol=
d the film hostage. This has been going on awhile under the radar, and the =
back-and-forth between Netflix and the estate is ongoing, with two sources =
telling me Netflix is confident a compromise can still be worked out. But s=
o far, no deal. And no deal means no Prince movie.           <br/> <br/>A h=
uge bummer, but this situation wasn=E2=80=99t entirely unforeseeable. <i>O.=
J.: Made in America</i>, which was originally commissioned as a five-hour, =
three-part installment of ESPN=E2=80=99s 30 for 30 series, eventually clock=
ed in at nearly eight hours. It=E2=80=99s still the longest film to ever wi=
n an Oscar (no, Netflix=E2=80=99s <i>The
Power of the Dog</i> just <i>felt</i> like it was eight hours), and it caus=
ed the Academy to ban =E2=80=9Cmultipart or limited series=E2=80=9D films f=
rom future consideration. Edelman is said to be as unrelenting in his indep=
endence as he is meticulous in his filmmaking, so he=E2=80=99s not interest=
ed in a truncated version of the Prince project.       <br/> <br/>The estat=
e of Prince, who died without a will, also sounds like a nightmare to deal =
with for Netflix=E2=80=99s unscripted chief <b>Brandon Riegg</b>, documenta=
ry leader <b>Adam Del Deo</b>, and the Netflix lawyers. Riegg inherited thi=
s project from former docs chief <b>Lisa Nishimura</b>. And two years ago, =
a Minnesota probate settlement divided Prince=E2=80=99s estate in two: Prin=
ce=E2=80=99s family and friends created Prince Legacy, on the one hand, and=
 on the other, there=E2=80=99s Prince OAT Holdings, an arm of the rights ma=
nagement company Primary Wave Music. (Its president, <b>Larry Mestel</b>, d=
id not return my email.)<br/> <br/>Since the two
entities manage the estate together, both must agree on most big decisions =
related to Prince=E2=80=99s intellectual property. Nightmare. Further compl=
icating matters, members of Prince Legacy sued four of his other relatives =
earlier this year over claims they=E2=80=99re wrongfully trying to seize co=
ntrol of the entity. That suit was filed by McMillan, who owns a stake in P=
rince Legacy. Not surprisingly, some of the Prince people are said to care =
about certain things in the documentary, while others care about other stuf=
f.<br/> <br/>A legal mess, but can it be resolved? I hope so. One could arg=
ue that nine episodes on Prince is too many. To be honest, most of these mu=
ltipart documentary series would be well-served by a Harvey Scissorhands ed=
itor. Even Showtime=E2=80=99s highly regarded 2013 doc <i>History of The Ea=
gles</i> was able to tell the story of the famously dysfunctional band in j=
ust two, 90-minute episodes. And despite his place in music history, Prince=
 as a <i>story</i> probably
isn=E2=80=99t as interesting as O.J. There=E2=80=99s no true crime intrigue=
=E2=80=94we all know how Prince died=E2=80=94and it=E2=80=99s hard to point=
 to many music docs that have been massive hits. Maybe the estate is right =
and Prince doesn=E2=80=99t justify such an extended treatment.  <br/> <br/>=
But Edelman is the X factor here, having taken the most worked-over tabloid=
 figure, <b>O.J. Simpson</b>, and turned <i>Made in America</i> into a spri=
ngboard for searing cultural analysis. Given his track record as a director=
, it would be tragic if he=E2=80=99s forced to shelve this film, even if hi=
s ultimate vision doesn=E2=80=99t match the framework that was agreed upon.=
 You=E2=80=99d think the friends and family of Prince, who, during his life=
, famously defied industry rules and charted his own creative path, would b=
e sympathetic to that argument.     <br/></td>
         </tr>
